# Button — React

**Docs:** [`docs/components/button/react/button-react.md`](../../../../docs/components/button/react/button-react.md) · **Visual spec:** [`docs/components/button/button-base.md`](../../../../docs/components/button/button-base.md)

Package: `@acko/button` · Directive: `"use client"`

## Architecture

Zero Tailwind in TSX — only `clsx` + `acko-*` classes. All styling in `@acko/css/button.css`.

## Props

See `ButtonProps` in `packages/button/src/Button.tsx` — `variant`, `size`, `loading`, `iconLeft`, `iconRight`, `iconOnly`, `fullWidth`, `type`, `children`; extends `Omit<ButtonHTMLAttributes<HTMLButtonElement>, "type">` (includes `className`, `disabled`, etc.).

## Canonical pattern

Match **`packages/button/src/Button.tsx`** exactly for DOM: `acko-btn-content`, `acko-btn-label`, `acko-btn-dots` + three `acko-btn-dot`, `sr-only` for icon-only children and loading text.

## Rules

- `isDisabled = disabled || loading`
- `aria-busy` when loading; `aria-disabled` when disabled or loading
- Icons + dots: `aria-hidden="true"`
- See **button-react.md** for imports, a11y table, responsive notes

## Dependencies

`clsx` (dependency), `react` / `react-dom` (peer ≥18), `lucide-react` (peer, optional — icons passed by consumer)
